          "a": "Because autoscaling has dead time it cannot configure away: a sampling interval, a decision, then provision, boot, app warmup, and a passing health check, which together run into minutes. A spike that arrives inside that window is a spike you cannot scale into in time. Headroom is the pre-provisioned capacity that absorbs it. You size it from boot time multiplied by the peak arrival-rate slope, and you trade it explicitly against the dollar cost of idle machines."
